line_1: On what fleet nerves the greyhound flys!
line_2: Hard is my lot, the hound replys,

line_1: Away the Fiend like Lightning flys,
line_2: And all his Wit to Work applys:
Mangled he falls, he howls and dyes.

line_1: And on the greedy tyrant flys:
line_2: The prostrate game a Lyon spys,

line_1: Fair as the Doves which o're our Cottage flys,
line_2: Soft as their Down, and just such lovely Eyes.

line_1: Protect me from these teazing flys!
line_2: She frowns, she frets. Good Gods, she crys,

line_1: Nor murder wasps, like vulgar flys,
line_2: Strike him not, Jenny, Doris crys,

line_1: He left the Room, th inquiring Mother flys
line_2: To ask what hopes, examines first his Eyes,
